1961;;The Singer Not the Song;;British;;Roy Ward Baker;;Dirk Bogarde, John Mills;;western;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Singer_Not_the_Song;;A priest, Father Michael Keogh (John Mills), is sent by Rome to Quantana, a remote Mexican town which is under the control of a ruthless bandit, Anacleto Komachi (Dirk Bogarde). Anacleto is educated and intelligent, and is "down" on the Church, but he finds in Keogh a man he strangely admires and with whom he can have intelligent conversation. However, he does not allow this to distract him from his goal: to expunge the priest from his fiefdom at any cost.